Molecular Weight Find genes whose unmodified protein product has a molecular weight within a range that you specify. Find genes whose unmodified protein product has a molecular weight within a range that you specify. 

 Molecular weights are machine calculated from the raw translation and do not take into account any protein or residue modifications. For translations containing ambiguous amino acid codes (B, Z, X) the calculation uses the average of the upper and lower bound of the molecular weight.

Inputs\:
    url - The REST API base url.
    username - The username used for URL authentication.
    password - The password used for URL authentication.
    authType - The type of authentication used by this operation when trying to execute the request on the target server. The authentication is not preemptive\: a plain request not including authentication info will be made and only when the server responds with a 'WWW-Authenticate' header the client will send required headers. If the server needs no autentication but you specify one in this input the request will work nevertheless. There client cannot choose the authentication method and there is no fallback so you have to know which one you need and you can specify only one.
Default value\: basic
Valid values\: basic, digest, ntlm, kerberos, any, ""
    proxyHost - The proxy server used to access the web site.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port.
    proxyUsername - The user name used when connecting to the proxy.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the "proxyUsername" input value.
    paramOrganism - Organism Select organism(s) you wish to query against. Click the [+] to expand taxon groupings. A default strain is choosen where there are multiple strains for a species.
